{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1998 |Team=South Carolina Gamecocks |Image=South Carolina Gamecocks wordmark.svg |ImageSize=150 |Conference=Southeastern Conference |Division=Eastern Division |ShortConference=SEC |CoachRank= |APRank= |BCSRank= |Record=1-10 |ConfRecord=0-8 |HeadCoach=[[Brad Scott (American football)|Brad Scott]] |OffCoach= |DefCoach= |OScheme= |DScheme= |StadiumArena=[[Williams-Brice Stadium]] (c. 80,250, grass) |Champion= |BowlTourney= |BowlTourneyResult= }} {{1998 SEC football standings}} The '''1998 South Carolina Gamecocks football team''' represented the [[University of South Carolina]] in the [[Southeastern Conference]] during the [[college football]] [[1998 NCAA Division I-A football season|season of 1998-1999]]. The Gamecocks were led by head coach [[Brad Scott (American football)|Brad Scott]] and played their home games in [[Williams-Brice Stadium]] in [[Columbia, South Carolina]]. Brad Scott was fired following the end of the season, but was quickly hired as an assistant coach by [[Clemson Tigers football|Clemson]]. [[Lou Holtz]] was subsequently hired as the new USC head coach.
